		section.pb-0.dolinks
			div.row
				div.col
					h4 Description

					p Time’s Up! is a fun, visual countdown timer for iPhone, iPad, Mac, and Apple TV. Whether it's for you, your kids, or someone else, Time’s Up! makes counting down more engaging — no more boring white numbers on a black background.

					p Time’s Up! was originally built for the developer's toddler. Timers are a great way to signal that it's almost time to stop doing something fun without becoming the "bad guy" — kids have more respect for what the phone says than what a parent says. The iPhone's built-in timer is very basic, so Time’s Up! makes it more fun and full-featured.

					p Time’s Up! has 7 styles to choose from:

					ul
						li <strong>Reveal</strong> — uncover a photo from your Photo Library as the seconds tick down.
						li <strong>Pixelate</strong> — a photo becomes clearer as the timer gets closer to zero.
						li <strong>Puzzle</strong> — a photo is broken into jigsaw pieces that fall into place as time progresses.
						li <strong>Gradient</strong> — a color-changing style that’s great for drawing your eye.
						li <strong>Clockface</strong> — a cute character who blinks, winks, and grins as your timer counts down.
						li Two <strong>classic clock face</strong> styles for a more traditional look.

					p All styles can be customized with their own alert sound and color.

					p Time’s Up! is great for:

					ul
						li Adults who need to be reminded to take a break from working.
						li Kids who don't want to do their homework but can be convinced to work in smaller chunks.
						li Setting reading or other activity timers before bedtime.
						li Helping kids with ADHD and similar conditions focus on an activity for a set amount of time.
						li Exercise groups — put a full-screen timer on your TV via AirPlay.
						li Anything that's based on a specific amount of time!

					p Other key features:

					ul
						li <strong>Guided Access</strong> — prevent kids from switching apps or changing timers. Only you have the power to stop the clock.
						li <strong>AirPlay and Apple TV</strong> — put a timer on the big screen for group activities.
						li <strong>iCloud sync</strong> — timers sync between iPhone, iPad, Mac, and Apple TV.
						li <strong>Shortcuts support</strong> — schedule and automate timers with the Shortcuts app.
						li <strong>Focus mode integration</strong> — use timers as part of a focused work session.
						li <strong>Apple Shortcuts</strong> — automate timers with Siri and Shortcuts workflows.
						li <strong>VPP / Education</strong> — available via Apple School Manager for classroom use.

					p Time’s Up! is a free download with a one-time in-app purchase that unlocks unlimited timers. There are no subscriptions, no ads, and no data collection of any kind.


